@page "/components/layouts/no-layout"
@attribute [NoLayout]
@inherits PageBase

<div style="padding: 40px; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;">
    <h1>[NoLayout]</h1>
    <p>
        Zero chrome — no <code>MainLayout</code>, no <code>DemoBoxLayout</code>, no
        wrapping <code>&lt;LayoutView&gt;</code>. The HTML you see above (right after
        the <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> tag) is whatever this page emits directly.
    </p>
    <p>
        Use cases: embeddable widgets, OAuth popups, framed third-party content,
        diagnostic pages, error pages that must work even when the main layout's
        injected services crash.
    </p>
    <p>
        Authorization still applies: <code>[Authorize]</code> /
        <code>[RequirePermission]</code> on this class would be honoured by
        <code>ZonitRouteView</code>'s wrapped <code>AuthorizeRouteView</code>.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="/components/layouts">← Back to layout demo</a>
    </p>
</div>
